dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.commonstructure.serviceneeds

Interface IDoIpRoutingActivationAuthenticationNeeds

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDoIpServiceNeeds, IEntity, IIdentifiable, IReferrable, IServiceNeeds

    public interface IDoIpRoutingActivationAuthenticationNeeds
extends IEntity, IDoIpServiceNeeds
    IDoIpRoutingActivationAuthenticationNeeds: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    DoIPRoutingActivationAuthenticationNeeds indicates that the software-component owning this ServiceNeeds will have an authentication required for a DoIP routing activation service (0x0005) according to ISO 13400-2:2012.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getDataLengthRequest

        long getDataLengthRequest()
        Query the value of the attribute DataLengthRequest.

        Describes the length in byte of the additional information for RA authentication that is needed by the software entity. If the software entity is a software-component the attribute does not need to exist as the information is available via the length of the uint8 Array type. Otherwise (i.e the software entity is a Complex Driver) this attribute needs to be filled out if additional information is needed.

        Returns:
        The value or null

      • getRoutingActivationType

        java.lang.String getRoutingActivationType()
        Query the value of the attribute RoutingActivationType.

        Describes the ISO 13400-2:2012 "routing activation request activation type" which is received via DoIP service 0x0005. 0x00 is DEFAULT, 0x01 is WWH-OBD. If neither of the specified values (0x00 or 0x01) is needed the token shall contain RA_ + hex value representation of the integer value shall be used (i.e: RA_0xE1).

        Returns:
        The value or null
